  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>green</strong> <strong>chilli[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Tip: Not a fan of spice? Remove the seeds!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>beef stock mix</strong> in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[500ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>garam masala</strong> and <strong>ground coriander</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>spiced beef stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add your <strong>lean beef mince </strong>to the pan with your <strong>tomato paste</strong> and<strong> roasted garlic paste</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once beginning to brown, add your <strong>basmati rice </strong>and the <strong>spiced beef stock</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Bring to the boil, then cook, covered, for a further 10-12 min or until the rice has fully absorbed the water and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the rice has absorbed all the liquid and the lean beef is cooked through, add your <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>aromatic lean beef pilaf</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Add your blanched peas to a colander and pour boiled water all over them to refresh them and serve to the side!</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/aromatic-lean-beef-pilaf-with-green-tomato-chutney-and-yoghurt/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve your <strong>aromatic</strong> <strong>lean</strong> <strong>beef pilaf </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, then dollop over your <strong>green tomato chutney </strong>and garnish with the <strong>green chilli rounds </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the green chilli rounds and green tomato chutney!</span></strong></p><p>Taste for seasoning, adding more<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> if needed</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
